Defendant Michael Wayne Lengling in court, in custody, with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern Konrad Paczuski and Lucas Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 is dismissed by operation of law.    Penalty enhancer on Count 2 struck by Court upon motion of the State.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

6 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 41 days )
- 3 Years of Initial Confinement
- 3 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Take a Cognitive Thinking Course;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- No contact with establishments with primary business serves alcohol;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

Fine : $2531.00 
DNA surcharge: $250.00
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $60.00 to be paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to  Butler Police Department.
(To be paid at the rate of $100.00  per month commencing 3rd month of release onto extended supervision.)

DL REVOCATION:  3 years

IGNITITION INTERLOCK: 3 years

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
